## ElevenLabs — Conversational AI (Voice Coach)

Used for the back-and-forth Voice Coach feature. The agent is configured server-side using the ElevenLabs SDK or REST API. The mode (Interview / Debate / Presentation / Impromptu) is passed as a system prompt parameter or agent config — never hardcoded per-mode.

---

## Supabase Schema

**sessions table:** `id`, `created_at`, `user_name`, `topic`, `duration_seconds`, `transcript`, `counter_feedback`, `grammarian_feedback`, `evaluator_feedback`, `evaluator_score` (int 0–10), `filler_word_count`

**action_points table:** `id`, `created_at`, `user_name`, `points` (text[]), `completed` (bool)

---

## Environment Variables

These live in `.env.local` only — never commit this file.

```env
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
```

- `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GROQ_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` — server-side only, never prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` keys are safe for the client but still must not contain secrets
